    • testGetGradient

      public void testGetGradient() throws GeoTessException
      Performs GeoTessModel gradient calculation at a specific grid node location and validates the result against a previously validated true result. Both linear and natural-neighbor interpolation types are tested as attribute gradients and their reciprocal attributes. The results are reported at an arbitrary interpolation location (lat, lon, depth = 5.5, 5.5, 369.0).
      Throws:
      GeoTessException
